1
00:00:10,125 --> 00:00:15,083
[man] <i>Pangu separates heaven and earth,</i>
<i>so that all things may flourish.</i>

2
00:00:15,166 --> 00:00:19,666
<i>One thousand years ago,</i>
<i>demonic flames surged to the heavens.</i>

3
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:23,458
<i>Hell's Demon King, Vasavatti,</i>
<i>barged into the Human Realm,</i>

4
00:00:23,541 --> 00:00:25,791
<i>and devoured living beings,</i>

5
00:00:25,875 --> 00:00:28,166
<i>increasing his demonic power.</i>

6
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:31,500
<i>The Crown Prince,</i>
<i>a god from the Celestial Realm,</i>

7
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:34,833
<i>descended to the world</i>
<i>to subdue this demon,</i>

8
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:38,750
<i>and return him to the hell</i>
<i>from which he came.</i>

9
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:43,708
<i>In the ensuing war,</i>
<i>the Human Realm was torn apart.</i>

10
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:47,125
<i>Thereafter, the Celestial Realm</i>
<i>established a rule</i>

11
00:00:47,208 --> 00:00:49,500
<i>that neither a god nor a demon</i>

12
00:00:49,583 --> 00:00:52,208
<i>can enter the Human Realm</i>
<i>in their true form.</i>

13
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:53,958
[growls]

14
00:00:54,041 --> 00:00:58,541
<i>Since then, any god or demon</i>
<i>who wishes to enter the Human Realm</i>

15
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:02,666
<i>can only do so by channeling</i>
<i>their spirits through humans.</i>

16
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:06,708
<i>And only a few humans are equipped</i>
<i>to be their supernatural agents.</i>

17
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:09,291
- [grunts]
- [dramatic music playing]

18
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,791
[groans]

19
00:01:24,875 --> 00:01:27,166
<i>Some of these</i>
<i>supernatural agents are endowed</i>

20
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:29,750
<i>with immense power and responsibility.</i>

21
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,208
[battle cries]

22
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:32,375
<i>They are called…</i>

23
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:36,916
<i>…agents from above.</i>

24
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,416
AGENT FROM ABOVE

25
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,500
[theme music playing]

26
00:01:42,291 --> 00:01:47,083
THE SINNER

27
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,791
[thunder cracking]

28
00:01:52,791 --> 00:01:59,791
{\an8}DONGFENG MARKET

29
00:02:00,916 --> 00:02:02,916
[low, eerie music playing]

30
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:14,041
[snoring]

31
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:27,375
Can I ask you a question?

32
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:31,500
[man continues snoring]

33
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,916
If you be human, stop there.

34
00:02:43,083 --> 00:02:45,083
Or are you a ghost?

35
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,416
[snores]

36
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:50,583
[thunder cracking]

37
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:13,083
[eerie music continues]

38
00:03:22,291 --> 00:03:24,291
[growls in the background]

39
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:43,791
[eerie music continues]

40
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:54,583
UNIT 4-9 NO. 56 LANE 114 DONGFENG ST.
MASTER HAN CHIEH

41
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,958
[growls intensify]

42
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:18,958
UNIT 4-9 NO. 56 LANE 114 DONGFENG ST.

43
00:04:21,583 --> 00:04:22,958
[doorbell rings]

44
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:27,583
- [man] Who is it?
- Are you Han Chieh?

45
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:42,458
[Han] What do you want?

46
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:45,500
Hello, Master Han. I'm Yeh Tzu.

47
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:47,791
I'm told you can help
with ghosts and spiri--

48
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:50,458
- Sorry, I don't take on new--
- Hang on. Please wait.

49
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:52,791
I know you only do the work
of the Crown Prince.

50
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,875
But there's nowhere else for me to turn.

51
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:59,625
- This was placed under my father's pillow.
- [sniffs]

52
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:01,416
The ghost was a woman.

53
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:08,291
Go away and don't bother me again.

54
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:11,291
[door slams]

55
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:16,291
[ringing doorbell repeatedly]

56
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:18,625
Didn't you hear me? I told you to go.

57
00:05:20,875 --> 00:05:22,166
Why are you so cruel?

58
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:24,958
Maybe you're not a master.
You're just a pretender!

59
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:27,708
I told you to go away. Now go!

60
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,791
[loud ticking]

61
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:37,208
[crackling]

62
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:42,458
[dramatic music playing]

63
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,208
[music intensifies]

64
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:04,083
- [Yeh] Hey!
- [Han] Come with me!

65
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,083
What are you doing?

66
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:22,000
[theme music playing]

67
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:32,166
[ghosts growling]

68
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:42,625
[music fades]

69
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,958
Hey, you there. How old are you?

70
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:09,291
Uh, 21.

71
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:11,666
- [whimsical music playing]
- [scoffs]

72
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,333
When are you free again?

73
00:07:21,125 --> 00:07:22,541
I'm not sure.

74
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:25,000
She's only 21.

75
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:28,583
Be nice to her or the heavens
will punish you.

76
00:07:29,625 --> 00:07:30,708
I'm off then.

77
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:33,125
I'll see you next time.

78
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:35,416
[door opens and closes]

79
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,333
[whimsical music continues]

80
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:45,333
[lighter clicking]

81
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:50,125
[chirps softly]

82
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:53,291
What now, you lousy bird?

83
00:07:59,791 --> 00:08:03,333
I still have work to do,
and you won't even let me smoke?

84
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,208
[bell rings]

85
00:08:05,291 --> 00:08:06,541
Thanks a lot.

86
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:08,916
[music ends]

87
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:14,833
[sighs]

88
00:08:17,541 --> 00:08:18,750
[Yeh Tzu] Master Han.

89
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:23,708
A feng shui master haunts my mother.

90
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,958
And so he wants to harm
my father with this.

91
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:27,875
It's a fake.

92
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:29,541
No, it's real.

93
00:08:30,375 --> 00:08:32,666
I've seen it myself many times.

94
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:35,333
He practices the technique
of Wumeng Maoshan.

95
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,416
[dramatic music playing]

96
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:39,416
Wumeng Maoshan?

97
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,458
HO CHUN-LAI

98
00:08:51,708 --> 00:08:55,250
ONLY SUCCESSOR OF WUMENG MAOSHAN TECHNIQUE
PASSED DOWN FROM MASTER CHEN CHI-SHA

99
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:07,375
{\an8}WUMENG OCCULTIST DRIVES
WHITE-CLOTHED FEMALE GHOST TO HARM PEOPLE

100
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:10,000
[dramatic music continues]

101
00:09:10,083 --> 00:09:13,083
- Why didn't you show me this earlier?
- Do you know him?

102
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:15,375
No, I don't.

103
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:17,958
PASSED DOWN FROM MASTER CHEN CHI-SHA

104
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:20,791
But his master, Chen Chi-sha,
is quite famous.

105
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:26,375
[sighs]

106
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:29,875
It seems like your family is in trouble.
I have my orders.

107
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,625
You take your orders
from the Crown Prince?

108
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:33,958
[exhales]

109
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:36,041
Take me to your house tomorrow.

110
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:37,666
Thank you, Master Han!

111
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:39,958
Don't call me "Master".

112
00:09:40,458 --> 00:09:42,375
I'll just take a look. Nothing else.

113
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,250
Yes, Mr. Han.

114
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:48,375
What happened outside before?

115
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,166
[sighs]

116
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,625
[theme music builds]

117
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:54,916
There was once a man
in love with a woman who lived here.

118
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:58,833
<i>When the romance ended,</i>
<i>he set a fire so they'd die together.</i>

119
00:09:58,916 --> 00:09:59,916
[screams]

120
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,125
<i>In the end, he lived,</i>

121
00:10:01,208 --> 00:10:03,375
<i>but the residents here weren't so lucky.</i>

122
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:07,458
<i>Their unjust death destined them</i>
<i>to become earthbound spirits.</i>

123
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:09,541
And so they're stuck here.

124
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:13,708
Every night after 11p.m.,
they become frightened again.

125
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:18,208
They think he's returning
to set yet another fire like what you saw.

126
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,625
You get it?

127
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:30,125
[groans] Mr. Han, what was that for?

128
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:33,916
[music fades]

129
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:40,958
I'm opening your third eye,
so you won't startle my old neighbors.

130
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,083
[eerie music playing]

131
00:10:49,875 --> 00:10:51,875
[growls]

132
00:10:59,583 --> 00:11:01,666
I can see them, your neighbors.

133
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,458
[Han Chieh] It's okay.
Don't be frightened.

134
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:15,791
[Yeh Tzu chuckles nervously]

135
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:26,375
- [Yeh Tzu] Sorry to disturb you.
- [music ends]

136
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:31,166
{\an8}[siren wailing]

137
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:33,333
{\an8}TAIPEI CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT
CENTRAL DISTRICT PRECINCT

138
00:11:33,416 --> 00:11:34,625
{\an8}[telephone rings]

139
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:37,750
[man 1] <i>She was crying.</i>
<i>She was begging me to send her the money.</i>

140
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:41,375
[man 2] Sir, I don't recommend that.
Don't send any money.

141
00:11:41,458 --> 00:11:43,375
Let the police sort it out
when they arrive.

142
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:46,041
<i>What if it is true?</i>
<i>She said she's in love with me.</i>

143
00:11:46,125 --> 00:11:48,583
- Look. I'm not a mind reader, okay?
- [curious music playing]

144
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,208
I can only tell you what I know,

145
00:11:50,291 --> 00:11:52,708
that most people who behave
like this are scammers.

146
00:11:52,791 --> 00:11:53,625
- <i>She loves me.</i>
- [beep]

147
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:54,541
Hello?

148
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:58,041
You there? Hello, sir? You there?

149
00:11:59,041 --> 00:12:01,833
[sighs] Some people are so stupid.

150
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:04,333
[curious music continues]

151
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:11,791
Restroom Peeping Tom.
Cameras don't pick up anyone.

152
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:15,125
Ask Han Chieh to check for a ghost.

153
00:12:15,208 --> 00:12:19,000
[gasps] Any spirit causing trouble
will not escape my eyes.

154
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:23,166
[chuckles] Yeah, for sure.
You could see ghosts from birth.

155
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:27,083
Giving this case to you
seems only natural, hey?

156
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,708
Don't worry, Chao. Leave this case to me.

157
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:33,291
It's people I can't cope with,
but ghosts are easy enough.

158
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:34,708
- [door beeps]
- [music ends]

159
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:42,166
[door closes]

160
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:47,625
First time I saw her,
she was standing over there.

161
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:51,500
Then the second time, she was there.

162
00:12:51,583 --> 00:12:53,583
[suspenseful music plays]

163
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:55,875
[ghost screams]

164
00:13:02,791 --> 00:13:04,791
[tense music playing]

165
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:15,250
LAST TIME TRAVELING TO JAPAN
BEFORE GETTING SICK.

166
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:19,083
{\an8}LEAFY, YOU CAN DO IT!
GET BETTER SOON, BEAT YOUR ILLNESS!

167
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:22,250
[music fades]

168
00:13:22,333 --> 00:13:27,333
BEI KANG UNITED HOSPITAL, YEH CHIH-LING

169
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:31,333
[poignant piano playing]

170
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:33,666
Hey. There's nothing here.

171
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,291
Are you okay?

172
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:45,000
I have leukemia.

173
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:55,000
Look. Cool, hey?

174
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:59,458
[poignant music continues]

175
00:14:01,958 --> 00:14:02,791
Mmm.

176
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:08,833
[Yeh Tzu] I found that red packet here.

177
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:14,458
Strange, it's here again.

178
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:19,291
[music turns suspenseful]

179
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:30,000
No smell. It's fake.

180
00:14:30,083 --> 00:14:32,458
I don't understand. I know I saw her.

181
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:35,750
If there was a ghost,
I'd see it, and smell it too.

182
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:38,416
- [sniffs]
- This has no smell.

183
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,958
Perhaps you just imagined it.

184
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:42,750
[front door beeps]

185
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:44,541
Please come in, Master Ho.

186
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:46,500
I'm sorry to trouble you again.

187
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:48,083
[suspenseful music continues]

188
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:49,583
Yeh Tzu?

189
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,916
Oh. Is this your friend?

190
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:53,291
- Yes.
- Hello.

191
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:55,250
He's my senior at film school.

192
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:58,333
[Mrs. Yeh] I asked Master Ho
to come and give you a checkup.

193
00:14:58,416 --> 00:15:00,833
Have a seat. I'll slice up some fruit.

194
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:02,625
Come and help me.

195
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:04,416
Please.

196
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:06,500
[suspenseful music builds]

197
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:11,083
Master Ho, apart from feng shui,
you're a doctor too?

198
00:15:11,166 --> 00:15:12,166
[Ho Chun-lai scoffs]

199
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,250
I came to read her palms

200
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:17,291
to see how she can avoid disaster.

201
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,250
Disaster?

202
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,750
Like finding this?

203
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:23,500
How is Chen Chi-sha?

204
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:27,000
[exhales] Master Chen is long retired.

205
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:29,333
He sunbathes, enjoys life.

206
00:15:30,375 --> 00:15:35,791
This is to help Mrs. Yeh
save her relationship with her husband.

207
00:15:35,875 --> 00:15:38,500
I know about Wumeng Maoshan Technique.

208
00:15:39,208 --> 00:15:42,208
I should warn you. Be careful.

209
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:44,291
[suspenseful music continues]

210
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:50,166
You know, I only charge
for my services if I think I can help.

211
00:15:51,541 --> 00:15:53,666
I'm not here to cause trouble.

212
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,833
RED-CLOTHED FEMALE GHOST AND
WHITE-CLOTHED FEMALE GHOST HARM PEOPLE

213
00:16:05,916 --> 00:16:07,083
HSIAO-MING LINGERS IN WOMEN'S ROOM

214
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,666
Mr. Han, I don't trust that man.

215
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:16,750
Why are you back?

216
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:18,541
You should be resting.

217
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:24,083
I told my mother we were shooting a movie.

218
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:26,000
I convinced her to let me come out.

219
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:30,000
You can't hang out with me. I'm too busy.

220
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:32,333
How are you busy?

221
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:34,583
Is it for the Crown Prince?

222
00:16:34,666 --> 00:16:36,500
[excitedly] Can I come along too?

223
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:45,750
My house is still haunted.
I really need you.

224
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:48,000
Are you just going to abandon me?

225
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:51,041
That would make me very sad.

226
00:16:51,125 --> 00:16:53,541
You don't want me to make a scene, do you?

227
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:56,500
People will stare,
and think we're an angry couple fighting.

228
00:16:56,583 --> 00:16:58,583
[whimsical music playing]

229
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:03,083
You made a friend? Won't you introduce me?

230
00:17:04,916 --> 00:17:06,791
You're mistaken. She's a client.

231
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:09,750
- We're not close.
- Hi. He's wrong, we are friends.

232
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,500
[whimsical music continues]

233
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:15,333
[chuckles] Han is always funny.
His friend is my friend.

234
00:17:15,416 --> 00:17:16,500
So, what'll it be?

235
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:18,791
- I'll have spareribs.
- Two.

236
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:21,666
Sure.

237
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:26,416
[Han Chieh sighs]

238
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:29,083
[music fades]

239
00:17:32,375 --> 00:17:33,208
Who's she?

240
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:37,625
Hey, this is out of line.

241
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:40,083
- Isn't she underage?
- [intriguing music playing]

242
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:43,291
- He's helping me with my ghost.
- Oh, I need his help as well.

243
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:45,125
You eaten?

244
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,250
Not yet.

245
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:49,125
So, don't ask me anything
that puts me off my food.

246
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:50,083
[inhales]

247
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,083
I'm on a case.

248
